Description: Commercially prepared Indian style Rogan Josh flavoured sauce. Commonly contains water, vegetable oil, salt, coriander, ginger, chilli, spices, gram flour and pepper.

Name: Sauce, salsa, tomato-based, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared Mexican style, tomato based dip. Typical ingredients include tomato, onion, capsicum, jalapenos, salt and chilli.

Name: Sauce, simmer for chicken, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared simmer/bake sauce intended for use with chicken dishes. Typical base ingredients  include water, vegetable oil, onion, thickener, flavours, herbs and spices. Additional ingredients may be included depending on the flavour of the simmer sauce.

Name: Sauce, simmer, curry flavoured, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared simmer style sauce suitable for pouring over chicken or beef to produce an Indian-style curry.

Name: Sauce, soy, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared dark brown salty liquid sauce commonly containing hydrolysed soy protein, hydrolysed wheat protein, salt, colour (caramel) and water.

Name: Sauce, soy, commercial, reduced salt
Description: Commercially prepared dark brown, salty, liquid sauce commonly containing hydrolysed soy protein, hydrolysed wheat protein, salt, colour (caramel) and water. Reduced in salt compared to regular soy sauce.

Name: Sauce, tabasco, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared spicy sauce made from red peppers.

Name: Sauce, tomato, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared sauce with a thick consistency. Contains tomatoes, sugar, salt, food acid and spices.

Name: Sauce, tomato, commercial, reduced salt
Description: Commercially prepared sauce with a thick consistency formulated to have less added salt than regular commercial tomato sauce. Contains tomatoes, sugar, salt, food acid and spices.

Name: Sauce, white, savoury, homemade
Description: Home prepared creamy style sauce made in the home from  butter, white wheat flour and milk.

Name: Sauce, Worcestershire, commercial
Description: Commercially prepared fermented liquid condiment made with vinegar, molasses, golden syrup, salt, water, spices, soy sauce, pepper, tamarinds, anchovies, lemon oil, onion and garlic powder.

Name: Vinegar (except balsamic vinegar)
Description: Sour liquid prepared by acetous fermentation, with or without alcoholic fermentation, of any suitable foodstuff, commonly used in dressings. Available types of vinegar include white, brown and malt.

Name: Peanut butter, smooth & crunchy, added sugar & salt
Description: Commercial paste made from roasted and ground peanuts. Available in two types with (crunchy) and without (smooth) chunks of peanuts. Contains vegetable oil, added sugar and salt.

Name: Peanut butter, smooth & crunchy, no added sugar or salt
Description: Commercial paste made from roasted, unsalted and ground peanuts. Available in two types with (crunchy) and with out (smooth) chunks of peanuts. Does not contain added salt or sugar.

Name: Spread, yeast, marmite
Description: Commercial thick, dark brown concentrated yeast extract spread. Contains added salt, and vitamins B1, B2 and B3.

Name: Spread, yeast, vegemite
Description: Commercial, thick dark brown, salty concentrated yeast extract spread made by treating yeast with acid. Contains added salt, and vitamins B1, B2 and B3.

Name: Cheese, blue vein
Description: Prepared by the addition of culture, rennet and mould spores to cows milk to produce green, grey, blue or black spots of mould throughout the body of the cheese. Includes Australian and imported blue cheese.

Name: Cheese, brie
Description: Australian and imported soft cheese covered with white mould and labelled as being brie style or double brie. Prepared by pasteurising, culturing and coagulating cows milk prior to salting and curing.

Name: Cheese, camembert
Description: Prepared by pasteurising, culturing and coagulating cows milk prior to salting and curing to produce a soft creamy surface ripened cheese. Includes Australian and imported soft cheese covered with white mould and labelled as being camembert style.

Name: Cheese, cheddar, natural, regular fat
Description: Cheddar cheese prepared by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing to produce a hard pale yellow cheese. Includes unsliced mild, tasty and vintage varieties.

Name: Cheese, cheddar, natural, reduced fat (approximately 25%)
Description: Cheddar cheese prepared by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing to produce a hard pale yellow cheese. Formulated to have a fat content of approximately 25%.

Name: Cheese, cheddar, natural, reduced fat (approximately 15%)
Description: Cheddar cheese prepared by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing to produce a hard pale yellow cheese. Formulated to have a fat content of approximately 15%.

Name: Cheese, cheddar, processed, regular fat
Description: Commercially prepared regular fat processed cheddar cheese. Prepared by grinding, mixing, melting and emulsifying one or more varieties of cheese with salt to form a homogeneous mass. Supplied as slices or blocks.

Name: Cheese, cheddar, processed, reduced fat (approximately 15%), added vitamin D
Description: Commercially prepared processed cheddar cheese formulated to contain approximately 16% fat. Prepared by grinding, mixing, melting and emulsifying one or more varieties of cheese with salt and vitamin D to form a homogeneous mass. Supplied as slices or blocks.

Name: Cheese, cottage
Description: Regular fat creamed cottage cheese, prepared by curdling, salting, draining and washing cows milk to produce an unripened, white curd cheese.

Name: Cheese, cream, plain
Description: Regular fat soft, white cheese prepared by blending, culturing and salting cows milk, cream and vegetable gum.

Name: Cheese, edam
Description: A semi-hard cheese made by curdling cows milk with rennet, followed by curing. Coated in oil or a red or yellow wax film. Includes Australian and imported edam cheese.

Name: Cheese, fetta (feta)
Description: Made by curdling cows milk with rennet, which is then sliced, salted and stored in either whey or brine. Includes Australian and imported fetta cheese.

Name: Cheese, goat, firm
Description: Cheese made from goats milk. Firm in texture.

Name: Cheese, goat, soft
Description: Cheese made from goats milk. Soft in texture.

Name: Cheese, haloumi
Description: Salty, semi-soft cheese that maintains its texture when cooked.

Name: Cheese, mozzarella
Description: Cheese made from cows milk with a rubbery texture. Typically added to pizza and other Italian-style dishes.

Name: Cheese, parmesan, dried, finely grated
Description: Parmesan-style cheese, prepared by removing the majority of cream from cows milk before heating, curdling and brining. Cheese is finely grated prior to sale and some additional moisture may be removed, so that the cheese does not generally require refrigerator storage.

Name: Cheese, parmesan, fresh
Description: A hard granular cheese prepared by removing the majority of cream from cows milk before heating, curdling and brining. Cheese is shaved or coarsely grated prior to sale so that it is moister than finely grated parmesan cheese and requires refrigerator storage.

Name: Cheese, ricotta
Description: Australian produced ricotta cheese. Prepared by collecting the whey from the coagulation of cows milk and further separation and draining.

Name: Cheese, soy
Description: Cheese substitute produced using soy bean curd and other ingredients such as salt and thickeners. Includes hard and 'cream cheese' varieties.

Name: Cream, thickened, regular fat (approximately 35%)
Description: Australian produced thickened cream with a fat content of 35%. Major ingredients include cream, gelatine and vegetable gum. Produced by separating milk into a highly concentrated milk fat stream (cream) and a non-milk fat stream (skim milk) and adding thickener to increase the viscosity.

Name: Cream, imitation (non-dairy)
Description: Commercially produced soft product with a creamy appearance and texture that is commonly used in baked goods in place of whipped dairy cream, but which is not dairy-based.

Name: Cream, sour, regular fat
Description: Commercially produced Australian sour cream with a fat content of approximately 35% Prepared by culturing cream or milk with lactic acid bacteria resulting in the sour flavour.

Name: Cream, sour, light (approximately 18% fat)
Description: Commercially produced Australian sour cream with a fat content of approximately 18%. Prepared by culturing a combination of cows milk cream and milk with lactic acid bacteria resulting in the sour flavour and decreased fat content compared to regular sour cream.

Name: Ice cream, vanilla flavour, regular fat
Description: Commercial product prepared by mixing milk, sugar, gums, emulsifiers and vanilla flavour, then freezing rapidly with agitation to aerate the ice cream to give it a light texture. Includes varieties with a fat content of 11%. Some analysed samples contain egg yolk.

Name: Ice confection, stick, milk-based, various flavours
Description: Frozen flavoured ice confection typically made from sugar, skim milk/solids, whey and vegetable gums, sold on a stick. Include strawberry, banana and rainbow flavours.

Name: Ice confection, stick, water-based, various flavours
Description: Frozen water based ice confection made from sugar, food acid, vegetable gum, flavour and colour, sold on a stick.

Name: Ice confection, stick or tub, fruit juice or fruit flavoured
Description: Frozen fruit juice or fruit flavoured ice confection. typically made from sugar and fruit juices such as lemon, pineapple, passionfruit and orange. Frozen prior to sale and sold on a stick or in a tube. One of four samples does not contain fruit juice.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, regular fat (3.5% fat)
Description: Australian produced regular fat cows milk. Supplied with a minimum fat content of 3.2 g milk fat/100 g.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, regular fat (3.5% fat), added omega 3 polyunsaturates
Description: Australian produced regular fat cows milk to which sources of omega-3 fatty acids are added. Supplied with fat content of approximately 3.4%.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, reduced fat (1% fat)
Description: Australian produced reduced fat cows milk. Supplied with fat content of approximately 1%.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, reduced fat (1.5% fat), added omega 3 polyunsaturates
Description: Australian produced reduced fat cows milk. Supplied with a fat content of approximately 1.5%, with added sources of omega-3 fatty acids.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, skim (0.15% fat)
Description: Australian produced cows skim milk. Supplied with a maximum fat content of 0.15%.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, skim (0.15% fat), added milk solids
Description: Australian produced cows skim milk to which extra milk solids are added to increase calcium and protein content. Supplied with a maximum fat content of 0.15%.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, lactose free, regular fat (3.5% fat)
Description: Australian produced regular fat cows milk. Lactase enzyme added to pre-digest naturally-occurring lactose. Supplied with a fat content of 3.5%.

Name: Milk, cow, fluid, lactose free, reduced fat (1% fat)
Description: Australian produced regular fat cows milk. Lactase enzyme added to pre-digest naturally-occurring lactose. Supplied with a fat content of 1%.

Name: Milk, cow, canned, evaporated, regular
Description: Canned milk prepared by evaporating approximately 60% of the water content of regular fat cows milk prior to sterilisation.

Name: Milk, cow, canned, evaporated, reduced fat (approximately 2% fat)
Description: Canned milk prepared by evaporating approximately 60% of the water content of regular fat and skim cows milk prior to sterilisation. Formulated to have a fat content of 2%.

Name: Milk, cow, canned, sweetened, condensed, regular
Description: Milk product prepared by adding sugar to regular fat cows milk prior to evaporation of approximately 50% of the water content. Includes both canned and tube varieties.

Name: Milk, powder, cow, regular fat, unfortified
Description: Regular fat cows milk powder, prepared by removing water from regular fat milk by spray-drying. May also contain lecithin.

Name: Milk, powder, cow, regular fat, added vitamins A & D
Description: Regular fat cows milk powder, prepared by removing water from regular fat milk by spray-drying. Contains added vitamins A and D. May also contain lecithin.

Name: Milk, powder, cow, skim
Description: Cows skim milk powder, prepared by removing the majority of water from regular fat cows milk by spray drying.

Name: Milk, human/breast, mature, fluid
Description: Mammary secretion of human mothers.

Name: Custard, vanilla, regular fat
Description: Commercially produced regular fat vanilla flavoured custard. Major ingredients include regular fat milk, sugar, flavour and thickener. Custard does not contain eggs.

Name: Custard powder, vanilla, dry mix
Description: Dry yellow powder used for making custard. Ingredients include cornflour, salt, colours and flavours.

Name: Custard, vanilla, prepared from dry mix
Description: Vanilla custard prepared from commercial vanilla custard powder according to packet instructions.

Name: Dairy or yoghurt dessert, chocolate, regular fat
Description: Commercially prepared, dairy product flavoured with chocolate and intended for use as a child's dessert. Typical ingredients include milk, sugar, cocoa, vegetable gums, salt, thickeners, emulsifiers and flavours.

Name: Yoghurt, natural, regular fat (3% fat)
Description: Unflavoured (natural) yoghurt. Prepared by pasteurising and homogenising milk of various fat levels before culturing, resulting in a thickened, tangy yoghurt. Contains added milk powder. Formulated to have a fat content of approximately 4%. Does not contain fruit or flavouring.

Name: Yoghurt, apricot pieces or flavoured, regular fat (3% fat)
Description: Yoghurt with apricot pieces or flavour and added sugar. Prepared by culturing regular fat cows milk, resulting in a thickened, tangy yoghurt. Formulated to have a fat content of approximately 3%.

Name: Yoghurt, strawberry pieces or flavoured, regular fat (3% fat)
Description: Yoghurt with strawberry pieces or flavour and added sugar. Prepared by culturing regular fat cows milk, resulting in a thickened, tangy yoghurt. Formulated to have a fat content of approximately 3%.

Name: Yoghurt, vanilla flavoured, (2% fat)
Description: Yoghurt that is sweetened and flavoured with vanilla. Prepared by culturing regular fat cows milk, resulting in a thickened, tangy yoghurt. Formulated to have a fat content of approximately 2%.

Name: Yoghurt, vanilla flavoured, low fat (less than 0.5% fat)
Description: Low fat yoghurt that is sweetened and flavoured with vanilla. Prepared by culturing low fat milk, resulting in a thickened, tangy yoghurt. Formulated to have a fat content of <0.5%.

Name: Oat beverage, fluid, unfortified
Description: A dairy milk substitute made from filtered water, oats, sunflower oil and salt, without added vitamins and minerals.

Name: Oat beverage, fluid, added calcium
Description: A dairy milk substitute made from filtered water, oats, sunflower oil and salt. Contains added calcium.

Name: Rice beverage, fluid, added calcium
Description: A dairy milk substitute made from filtered water, brown rice, sunflower oil and salt. Contains added calcium.

Name: Soy beverage, regular fat (3% fat), unfortified
Description: A dairy milk substitute prepared from soy beans with a fat content of 3%. Does not contain added vitamins, minerals or artificial flavouring substances.

Name: Soy beverage, regular fat (3% fat), added Ca
Description: A dairy milk substitute prepared from soy beans with a fat content of 3%. Contains added calcium.

Name: Soy beverage, regular fat (3% fat), added Ca & vitamins A, B1, B2 & B12
Description: A dairy milk substitute prepared from soy beans with a fat content of 3%. Contains added calcium and vitamins A, B1, B2 and B12.

Name: Soy beverage, reduced fat (1% fat), added Ca & vitamins A, B1, B2 & B12
Description: A dairy milk substitute prepared from soy beans with a reduced fat content of ~1%. Contains added calcium, potassium, magnesium, vitamins A, B1, B2 and B12.

Name: Sausage, vegetarian style, unfortified, raw
Description: Sausages made from chopped, minced, or blended vegetables and/or legumes and other ingredients such as spices, sugar and salt. Does not contain added vitamins or minerals.

Name: Sausage, vegetarian style, added Fe, Zn and vitamin B12, raw
Description: Sausages made from chopped, minced, or blended vegetables and/or legumes and other ingredients such as spices, sugar and salt. Contains added iron, zinc and vitamin B12.

Name: Sausage, vegetarian style, fried, no added fat
Description: Sausages made from chopped, minced, or blended vegetables and/or legumes and other ingredients such as spices, sugar and salt. May contain added iron, zinc and vitamin B12. Cooked by frying with out added fat.

Name: Tofu (soy bean curd), firm, as purchased
Description: Commercially prepared soy bean extract, that has set to a firm texture. Ingredients include water, soy beans, glucono-delta lactone, and nigari (magnesium chloride).

Name: Yoghurt, soy based, berry flavoured, regular fat (3% fat)
Description: Yoghurt-style sweet product based on soy milk rather than dairy milk, with added berry flavour and formulated to have a fat content of approximately 3%..

Name: Yoghurt, soy based, vanilla flavoured, reduced fat (1% fat)
Description: Yoghurt-style sweet product based on soy milk rather than dairy milk, with added vanilla flavour and formulated to have a fat content of approximately 1%.

Name: Butter, plain, salted
Description: A product derived exclusively from milk and products obtained from milk, principally in the form of an emulsion of the type water-in-oil, containing no less than 80% milk fat. Contains added salt.

Name: Butter, plain, no added salt
Description: A product derived exclusively from milk and products obtained from milk, principally in the form of an emulsion of the type water-in-oil, containing no less than 80% milk fat. Does not contain added salt.

Name: Ghee, clarified butter
Description: Indian-style clarified butter containing at least 99.7% milk fat, used mainly in cooking.

Name: Dairy blend, butter & edible oil spread (approximately 80% fat), sodium 600 mg/100 g
Description: A spread that is a blend of approximately two-thirds butter and one-third vegetable oil, generally canola oil, with a fat content of approximately 80%. Contains added salt and vitamins A and D.

Name: Dairy blend, butter & edible oil spread (approximately 80% fat), reduced salt (sodium 400 mg/100 g)
Description: A spread that is a blend of approximately two-thirds butter and one-third vegetable oil, generally canola oil with a fat content of approximately 80%. Contains a lower salt content than regular dairy blend and added vitamins A and D.

Name: Margarine spread, polyunsaturated (70% fat)
Description: A polyunsaturated edible oil spread containing approximately 70% fat, the majority of which are polyunsaturated edible oils (including sunflower oil). Contains added salt and vitamins A and D.

Name: Margarine spread, polyunsaturated (70% fat), reduced salt (sodium 280 mg/100 g)
Description: A polyunsaturated edible oil spread containing approximately 70% polyunsaturated edible oils (including sunflower oil). Formulated to have a reduced salt content. Contains added vitamins A and D.

Name: Margarine spread, monounsaturated (80% fat), rice bran oil, unfortified
Description: A monounsaturated edible oil spread containing approximately 80% rice bran oil. Contains added salt, but does not contain added vitamins or minerals.

Name: Margarine spread, monounsaturated (70% fat), reduced salt (sodium 350 mg/100 g), added phytosterols
Description: A monounsaturated edible oil spread containing approximately 70% monounsaturated edible oils including canola oil, olive oil or blends of monounsaturated oils. Formulated to have a reduced salt content. Contains added vitamins A and D and phytosterols.

Name: Margarine spread, monounsaturated (greater than 65% fat)
Description: A monounsaturated edible oil spread containing approximately 65%  or more edible oils including canola oil, olive oil or blends of monounsaturated oils. Contains added salt and vitamins A and D.

Name: Margarine spread, monounsaturated (greater than 65% fat), reduced salt (sodium 360 mg/100 g)
Description: A monounsaturated edible oil spread containing approximately 65% monounsaturated edible oils including canola oil, olive oil or blends of monounsaturated oils. Formulated to have a reduced salt content. Contains added vitamins A and D.

Name: Margarine spread, monounsaturated, reduced fat (55% fat) & salt (sodium 380 mg/100 g)
Description: A monounsaturated edible oil spread containing approximately 55% monounsaturated edible oils including canola oil, olive oil or blends of monounsaturated oils. Formulated to have a reduced salt content. Contains added vitamins A and D

Name: Margarine spread, monounsaturated, reduced fat (less than 65% fat)
Description: A monounsaturated edible oil spread containing <65% edible oils including canola oil, olive oil or blends of monounsaturated oils. Contains added salt and vitamins A and D.

Name: Margarine spread, olive oil blend (65% fat), reduced salt (sodium 360mg/100 g)
Description: A monounsaturated edible oil spread containing approximately 65% monounsaturated olive oil. Formulated to have a reduced salt content. Contains added vitamins A and D.

Name: Oil, almond
Description: Edible oil extracted from the almond (Prunus amygdalus).

Name: Oil, blend of monounsaturated vegetable oils
Description: Edible oil composed of a mixture, or blend, of various monounsaturated vegetable oils available in 2008. Blend composition in the analysed samples may not represent those available at other times. Oil may contain antioxidant.

Name: Oil, blend of polyunsaturated vegetable oils
Description: Edible oil composed of a mixture, or blend, of various polyunsaturated vegetable oils available in 2008. Blend composition in the analysed samples may not represent those available at other times. Oil may contain antioxidant.

Name: Oil, canola
Description: Edible oil extracted from the seeds of the canola plant (Brassica napus or Brassica campestris). Although derived from the same plant, canola oil is not rapeseed oil, and it is distinguished by low levels of erucic acid.

Name: Oil, cottonseed
Description: Edible oil derived from the seeds of the cotton plant.

Name: Oil, copha
Description: Solidified edible oil extracted from the coconut and used in baking.

Name: Oil, grapeseed
Description: Edible oil extracted from the seeds of grapes.

Name: Oil, linseed or flaxseed
Description: Edible oil extracted from linseeds/flaxseeds.

Name: Oil, mustard seed
Description: Edible oil extracted from the seeds of the mustard plant (Sinapsis alba and Brassica nigra).

Name: Oil, macadamia
Description: Edible oil extracted from the macadamia nut (Macadamia integrifolia).

Name: Oil, olive
Description: Edible oil pressed from the flesh of the fruit of the olive tree (Olea europaea). Most values are derived from oils produced in Spain or Italy and imported to Australia. Includes various grades of olive oil, such as 'pure' and 'extra virgin'.

Name: Oil, palm
Description: Edible oil extracted from the oil palm.

Name: Oil, peanut
Description: Edible oil extracted from the kernel of the peanut (Leguminosae Arachis hypogaea L.).

Name: Oil, rice bran
Description: Edible oil extracted from the bran of the rice kernel.

Name: Oil, soybean
Description: Edible oil extracted from the seeds of the soybean plant (Glycine maximus).

Name: Oil, sunflower
Description: Edible oil obtained from the seed of the sunflower plant (Helianthus annuus).

Name: Oil, vegetable
Description: Edible oil composed of a mixture, or blend, of monounsaturated and polyunsaturated vegetable oils. Oil may contain antioxidant.

Name: Dripping, beef
Description: Fat rendered from the meat, muscles and bones of beef.

Name: Fat, solid, vegetable oil based
Description: Solidified edible oil product prepared from a blend of vegetable oils, commonly used for frying. Blend composition may vary.

Name: Egg, chicken, whole, raw
Description: Edible portion, including yolk and white (albumen), of the egg of chickens. Uncooked.

Name: Egg, chicken, whole, hard-boiled
Description: Edible portion, including yolk and white (albumen), of the egg of chickens, boiled in unsalted water for 5-10 minutes until both yolk and white are firm.

Name: Egg, chicken, whole, poached
Description: Edible portion, including yolk and white (albumen), of the egg of chickens, simmered in acidified water for 3-5 minutes, then drained.

Name: Egg, chicken, whole, fried, no fat added
Description: Edible portion, including yolk and white (albumen), of the egg of chickens, fried without added fat, until the yolk is set.

Name: Egg, chicken, whole, omega-3 polyunsaturate enriched, raw
Description: Edible portion, including both yolk and white (albumen), of the egg of chickens fed a specific diet to increase the level of omega-3 polyunsaturated fatty acids. Actual levels of polyunsaturated fatty acids may vary depending on the chickens diet. Uncooked.

Name: Egg, chicken, whole, omega-3 polyunsaturate enriched, boiled
Description: Edible portion, including both yolk and white (albumen), of the egg of chickens fed a specific diet to increase the level of omega-3 polyunsaturated fatty acids. Actual levels of polyunsaturated fatty acids may vary depending on the chickens diet. Boiled in water until both yolk and albumen are set.

Name: Egg, chicken, whole, scrambled, with regular fat cows milk, no fat added
Description: Edible portion of chicken egg, including both yolk and white (albumen), beaten with regular fat cows milk and cooked by continuous stirring (scrambling) over low heat until just set. Does not contain added fat.

Name: Egg, chicken, white (albumen), raw
Description: White (albumen) portion of chicken eggs. Uncooked.

Name: Egg, chicken, white (albumen), hard-boiled
Description: White (albumen) portion of chicken eggs, separated from the yolk portion after being boiled in the shell in unsalted water.

Name: Egg, chicken, yolk, raw
Description: Yolk portion of chicken eggs, including any adhering white (albumin) portion. Uncooked.

Name: Egg, chicken, yolk, hard-boiled
Description: Yolk portion of chicken eggs, separated from the white (albumin) portion after being boiled in the shell in unsalted water.

Name: Apple, bonza, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with red skin and cream coloured flesh.

Name: Apple, dried
Description: Round shaped fruit with either a green or red waxy skin and cream/white coloured flesh. Peeled, cut (into rings or diced) and dried before packaging.

Name: Apple, fuji, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with red skin and cream coloured flesh.

Name: Apple, golden delicious, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with golden green skin and cream coloured flesh.

Name: Apple, granny-smith, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with green skin and cream/white coloured flesh.

Name: Apple, jonathon, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with red skin and cream/white coloured flesh.

Name: Apple, pink lady, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with pink/red skin and cream coloured flesh.

Name: Apple, red delicious, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with red skin and cream coloured flesh.

Name: Apple, royal gala, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with red skin and cream coloured flesh.

Name: Apple, red skin, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit with red/pink skin and cream/white flesh. Includes pink lady, red delicious, royal gala, fuji, jonathan and bonza varieties.

Name: Apricot, raw
Description: Small, orange coloured stone fruit.

Name: Apricot, dried
Description: Small, orange-coloured stone fruit dried prior to packaging. May be treated to prevent browning.

Name: Apricot, canned in pear juice
Description: Small, orange-coloured stone fruit canned in pear juice.

Name: Apricot, canned in pear juice, drained
Description: Small, orange-coloured stone fruit canned in pear juice, then drained.

Name: Apricot, canned in pear juice, juice only
Description: Pear juice from canned apricots.

Name: Banana, cavendish, peeled, raw
Description: Long cylindrical fruit with thick yellow skin and cream-coloured flesh.

Name: Banana, lady finger or sugar, peeled, raw
Description: Medium sized cylindrical fruit with a thick yellow skin and cream coloured flesh. Also known as sugar banana.

Name: Blackberry, raw
Description: Round fruit characterised by a collection of tiny, shiny, black drupelets around a central white core.

Name: Blueberry, raw
Description: Small, deep blue berry with whitish waxy bloom.

Name: Blueberry, purchased frozen
Description: Small, deep blue berry with whitish waxy bloom. Frozen prior to sale.

Name: Cherry, raw
Description: Small, deep reddish-purple stone fruit.

Name: Cherry, black, canned in syrup
Description: Small black cherries canned in sugar syrup.

Name: Cherry, black, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Small black cherries canned in sugar syrup, then drained.

Name: Cherry, black, canned in syrup, syrup only
Description: Syrup made from water and sugar, used in canned black cherries.

Name: Cumquat (kumquat), raw
Description: Small round orange fruit, similar in appearance to oranges but much smaller.

Name: Cranberry, raw
Description: A small, round, bright red berry with a tart flavour.

Name: Cranberry, dried, sweetened
Description: A small, round, bright red berry with a tart flavour, that has been dried (Craisins). Imported from the USA.

Name: Currant, dried
Description: Grapes that have been dried and packaged prior to sale.

Name: Custard apple, African pride, peeled, raw
Description: Light green to bluish green skin covered in irregular smooth bumps with white-cream flesh.

Name: Date, dried
Description: Small brown pitted dates that have been dried.

Name: Feijoa, raw
Description: Green fruit with wrinkled inedible peel, similar in size and shape to a kiwi fruit, with a sweet clear gelatinous seed pulp.

Name: Fig, dried
Description: Small pear shaped fruit with seedy sweet pulp that vary in colour from green to yellow, brown, purple or black that has been preserved by drying. Imported into Australia.

Name: Fig, fresh, unpeeled, raw
Description: Small pear shaped fruit with seedy sweet pulp that vary in colour from green to yellow, brown, purple or black.

Name: Fruit salad, canned in fruit juice
Description: A variety of fruits that have been canned in fruit juice.

Name: Fruit salad, canned in fruit juice, drained
Description: A variety of fruits that have been canned in fruit juice, then drained.

Name: Fruit salad, canned in fruit juice, juice only
Description: Fruit juice, used in canned fruit salad. Commonly used juices include apple, peach, pear and pineapple.

Name: Goji berry, dried
Description: Small oblong berries that range from dark pink to red in colour. Dried before packaging.

Name: Grape, black muscatel/muscat, raw
Description: Full bodied, seeded grape, with a black crisp skin and juicy pulp.

Name: Grape, black sultana, raw
Description: Oval, black, seedless grape with crisp texture.

Name: Grape, cornichon, raw
Description: Elongated, purple coloured grape.

Name: Grape, red globe, raw
Description: Large red-black seeded grape, with a crisp skin and juicy sweet pulp.

Name: Grape, thompson seedless or sultana, raw
Description: Medium-sized, oval shaped seedless grape with light green skin and pale green flesh.

Name: Grape, waltham cross, raw
Description: Elongated oval grape, with a golden green firm skin and a sweet juicy pulp.

Name: Grapefruit, peeled, raw
Description: Large, slightly tart citrus fruit. The rind is mostly yellow, and often tinged with green or red, with white pulp.

Name: Guava, Hawaiian, raw
Description: Round to oblong shaped green skinned tropical fruit with pink flesh.

Name: Jackfruit, peeled, raw
Description: Rough fruit with light-green to yellow skin, composed of small spiny segments with a short stem and yellow flesh.

Name: Kiwifruit, green (hayward), peeled, raw
Description: Oval shaped fruit with thin, brown, furry skin and green flesh. Imported from New Zealand.

Name: Kiwifruit, gold, peeled, raw
Description: Oval shaped fruit, tapering at one end, with thin, brown, furry skin and gold-coloured flesh. Imported from New Zealand.

Name: Lemon, peeled, raw
Description: Tart oval citrus fruit, with a yellow rind and pulp.

Name: Lemon peel, raw
Description: The peel (Limonis Cortex) and the rind (flavedo) of fresh lemons.

Name: Lemon, preserved
Description: Tart citrus fruit, with a yellow rind and pulp. Preserved in a lemon juice and salt brine. Typically, only the peel is consumed

Name: Lime, peeled, raw
Description: Tart round/oval citrus fruit with light greenish-yellow rind and pulp when ripe.

Name: Loquat, peeled, raw
Description: Small round yellow/orange fruit with white/yellow/orange flesh.

Name: Lychee, peeled, raw
Description: Small round to oval shaped fruit with a scaly reddish to reddish-brown skin and off-white flesh.

Name: Mandarin, peeled, raw
Description: Citrus fruit with an orange peel and flesh. Imperial cultivar of mandarin.

Name: Mandarin, canned in syrup
Description: Mandarin segments canned in sugar syrup.

Name: Mandarin, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Mandarin segments canned in sugar syrup, then drained.

Name: Mandarin, canned in syrup, syrup only
Description: Syrup made from water and sugar, used in canned mandarins.

Name: Mango, peeled, raw
Description: Tropical fruit with a smooth reddish to orange skin and orange flesh.

Name: Mango, pulped, canned
Description: Canned mango pulp. Contains added sugar.

Name: Melon, honey dew, white skin, peeled, raw
Description: White/cream skinned melon with green flesh.

Name: Melon, honey dew, yellow skin, peeled, raw
Description: Yellow skinned melon with white or green flesh.

Name: Melon, rockmelon, peeled, raw
Description: Round green skinned fruit with brown netting, orange flesh and a sweet and smooth texture.

Name: Melon, watermelon, peeled, raw
Description: Large oval fruit with a thick green skin and a pink to red flesh containing black seeds. Skin and seeds removed.

Name: Mixed dried fruit
Description: Mixture of various types of dried fruits such as sultanas, currants, citrus peel, raisins, cherries.

Name: Mulberry, raw
Description: Glossy dark red to black coloured berry with sweet juicy flavour.

Name: Nectarine, yellow, unpeeled, raw
Description: Small stone fruit with a reddish/orange skin and orange flesh.

Name: Orange, peeled, raw
Description: Round in shape with an orange waxy peel and orange flesh, that can be broken into segments.

Name: Orange, navel, peeled, raw
Description: Round in shape with an orange waxy peel and orange flesh, that can be broken into segments. Include Washington, Lanes Late and Leng navel oranges.

Name: Orange, valencia, peeled, raw
Description: Round in shape with an orange thin waxy peel and orange flesh, that can be broken into segments.

Name: Passionfruit, raw
Description: Pulp and seeds of purple skinned passionfruit.

Name: Passionfruit, pulp, canned
Description: Pulp and seeds of purple skinned passionfruit, canned passionfruit pulp.

Name: Pawpaw (papaya), peeled, raw
Description: Round orange skinned fruit with orange flesh with seeds.

Name: Peach, yellow, unpeeled, raw
Description: Small stone fruit with a reddish/orange furry skin and orange flesh.

Name: Peach, canned in pear juice
Description: Small stone fruit with a reddish/orange furry skin and orange flesh canned in pear juice.

Name: Peach, canned in pear juice, drained
Description: Small stone fruit with a reddish/orange furry skin and orange flesh canned in pear juice, then drained.

Name: Peach, canned in pear juice, juice only
Description: Pear juice used in canned peaches.

Name: Pear, Packham's triumph, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round pear shape with medium length neck, yellowish green skin and white flesh.

Name: Pear, William Bartlett, unpeeled, raw
Description: Round pear shape with medium length neck and slightly bumpy skin that is green to greenish yellow with white flesh.

Name: Pear, green skin, unpeeled, raw
Description: Long pear shape with tapering neck, a green skin and yellowish white flesh. Includes averaged weighted results of Peckham's Triumph, William Bartlett.

Name: Pear, brown skin, unpeeled, raw
Description: Long pear shape with tapering neck, brown skin and yellowish white flesh.

Name: Pear, canned in pear juice
Description: Fruit with a long pear shape with tapering neck, a brown or green skin and yellowish white flesh canned pear in pear juice.

Name: Pear, canned in pear juice, drained
Description: Fruit with a long pear shape with tapering neck, a brown or green skin and yellowish white flesh canned pear in pear juice, then drained.

Name: Pear, canned in pear juice, juice only
Description: Pear juice drained from pears canned in juice.

Name: Pear, nashi, unpeeled, raw
Description: A round fruit with a smooth, green-yellow or brownish-russet skin depending on variety, and a crisp texture. Appearance and size similar to that of an apple.

Name: Persimmon, peeled, raw
Description: Round to heart shaped fruit with bright orange skin and orange flesh.

Name: Pineapple (cayenne), peeled, raw
Description: Oval fruit with a thick greenish skin and yellow flesh. Leaves, skin, bracts and core removed.

Name: Pineapple, canned in pineapple juice
Description: Oval fruit with a thick greenish skin and yellow flesh. Leaves, skin, bracts and core removed. Sliced and canned in pineapple juice.

Name: Pineapple, canned in pineapple juice, drained
Description: Oval fruit with a thick greenish skin and yellow flesh. Leaves, skin, bracts and core removed. Sliced and canned in pineapple juice, then drained.

Name: Pineapple, canned in pineapple juice, juice only
Description: Pineapple juice, used in canned pineapples.

Name: Pineapple, canned in syrup
Description: Oval fruit with a thick greenish skin and yellow flesh. Leaves, skin, bracts and core removed. Sliced and canned in heavy syrup.

Name: Pineapple, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Oval fruit with a thick greenish skin and yellow flesh. Leaves, skin, bracts and core removed. Sliced and canned in heavy syrup, then drained.

Name: Pineapple, canned in syrup, syrup only
Description: Heavy sugar-based syrup used in canning of pineapple.

Name: Plum, unpeeled, raw
Description: Small round stone fruit with a deep purple skin and a reddish/purple flesh.

Name: Plum, dark, canned in syrup
Description: Satsuma or dark plums canned in sugar syrup.

Name: Plum, dark, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Satsuma or dark plums canned in sugar syrup, then drained.

Name: Plum, dark, canned in syrup, syrup only
Description: Syrup made from water and sugar, used in canned satsuma or dark plums.

Name: Pomegranate, peeled, raw
Description: Round shaped fruit, with hard, thick red skin, which is divided into large membrane segments containing bright red juicy seeds.

Name: Prickly pear, peeled, raw
Description: Smooth skinned cactus fruit with clusters of tiny hair like spines, pulpy flesh containing numerous small black seeds. Also known as Indian Fig; Mission Cactus.

Name: Prune (dried plum)
Description: A plum that has been dried before packaging with the pit removed.

Name: Quandong, fruit, flesh
Description: Small fruit with a waxy shiny red skin. Supplied commercially in frozen state with kernels removed.

Name: Quince, peeled, raw
Description: Tart pome fruit, with a bright golden yellow skin and flesh. Similar in appearance to a pear.

Name: Raisin
Description: Dried red grapes, dark brown in colour.

Name: Rambutan, raw
Description: Small fruit with either red or yellow skin with soft spines.

Name: Raspberry, raw
Description: Small round berries characterised by a collection of tiny, shiny red drupelets.

Name: Raspberry, purchased frozen
Description: Small round berries characterised by a collection of tiny, shiny red drupelets. Frozen prior to sale.

Name: Raspberry, canned in syrup
Description: Small round berries characterised by a collection of tiny, shiny red drupelets canned in sugar syrup.

Name: Raspberry, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Small round berries characterised by a collection of tiny, shiny red drupelets canned in sugar syrup, then drained.

Name: Raspberry, canned in syrup, syrup only
Description: Syrup made from water and sugar used in canned raspberries.

Name: Rhubarb, stalk, raw
Description: Long reddish/pink stem with large green leaves. Leaves removed.

Name: Strawberry, raw
Description: Small sweet red berry with small seeds on the exterior.

Name: Strawberry, purchased frozen
Description: Small sweet red berry with small seeds on the exterior. Frozen prior to sale.

Name: Strawberry, canned in syrup
Description: Small sweet red berry with small seeds on the exterior canned in sugar syrup.

Name: Strawberry, canned in syrup, drained
Description: Small sweet red berry with small seeds on the exterior canned in sugar syrup, then drained.

Name: Strawberry, canned in syrup, syrup only
Description: Syrup made from water and sugar, used in canned strawberries.

Name: Sultana
Description: Dried green grapes, dark brown in colour.

Name: Tamarillo, peeled, raw
Description: Small fruit with a smooth peel that can be purple, red, orange, or yellow. It has a black or orange flesh (the darker the peel, the darker the flesh) surrounding a nest of seeds

Name: Tangelo, peeled, raw
Description: Mandarin grapefruit cross. Cultivars include: Orlando, Minneola, Seminole and San Jucinto.

Name: Tangerine or tangor, peeled, raw
Description: Mandarin orange cross.

Name: Wax jambu, raw
Description: Pear-shaped fruit with bright to dark pink skin, white flesh and several large brown seeds. Also known as Java Apple; Rose Apple; Makopa; Wax Apple.

Name: Lime, native, fruit
Description: Small, round fruit with a bitter and tart citrus flavour, light green or yellow in colour. Supplied commercially in frozen state.

Name: Plum, davidson (native), flesh
Description: Small edible sour fruit with burgundy coloured flesh. Supplied commercially in frozen state.

Name: Plum, salted
Description: Dried plums cured with a mixture of salt, sugar and other ingredients.

Name: Baked beans, canned in tomato sauce
Description: Navy/haricot beans canned in tomato sauce. Contains added salt, sugar, food acids, maize thickener and flavour.

Name: Baked beans, canned in tomato sauce, reduced salt
Description: Navy/haricot beans canned in tomato sauce, and formulated to have a reduced salt content. Contains added salt, sugar, food acids, maize thickener and flavour.

Name: Bean, broad, dried
Description: Fresh seed, generally green in colour, removed from its pod. Uncooked.

Name: Bean, haricot, dried
Description: Small white bean, round to oval in shape. Dried and uncooked.

Name: Bean, haricot, dried, boiled, drained
Description: Small white beans, round to oval in shape that have been dried, then soaked overnight, before boiling in unsalted water and drained.

Name: Bean, lima, dried
Description: Flat kidney shaped bean which can be white or green, large or small. Dried and uncooked. Popularly called butter bean. Produced in USA, South America and Madagascar, imported into Australia.

Name: Bean, lima, dried, boiled, drained
Description: Flat kidney shaped bean can be white or green, large or small that have been dried, then soaked in water before boiling in unsalted water and draining. Slightly sweet flavour when cooked. Popularly called butter bean. Produced in USA, South America and Madagascar, imported into Australia.

Name: Bean, mung, whole, dried, uncooked
Description: Small, squarish, dark green beans. Whole, uncooked.

Name: Bean, red kidney, dried
Description: Kidney shaped bean either elongated or plump in shape ranging in colour from dusky pink to deep red. Dried and uncooked.

Name: Bean, red kidney, dried, boiled, drained
Description: Kidney shaped bean either elongated or plump in shape ranging in colour from dusky pink to deep red that have been dried, then soaked in water overnight before boiling in unsalted water and draining.

Name: Bean, red kidney, fresh, raw
Description: Fresh seed, generally red in colour, removed from its pod. Uncooked.

Name: Bean, red kidney, fresh, boiled, drained
Description: Fresh seeds, generally red in colour, removed from their pod, boiled in unsalted water without added fat, then drained.

Name: Bean, red kidney, canned, drained
Description: Kidney shaped bean either elongated or plump in shape ranging in colour from dusky pink to deep red, canned in sweetened brine, then drained.

Name: Chickpea, dried
Description: A small, round ball with an uneven surface, approximately 6-7 mm in size. Light to dark brown in colour with a thick seed coat.

Name: Chickpea, desi, dried, boiled, drained
Description: A small, round ball with an uneven surface, approximately 6-7 mm in size. Light to dark brown in colour with a thick seed coat, boiled with no added salt or fat.

Name: Chickpea, canned, drained
Description: Small round cream coloured legume which has been boiled and canned in brine, then drained.

Name: Lentil, French, hulled, dry
Description: Small, lens-shaped, edible pulse with a black/grey colour.

Name: Lentil, green, hulled, dry
Description: Small, lens-shaped, edible pulse with a dusty green/brown colour.

Name: Lentil, red, hulled, dry
Description: Small, lens-shaped, edible pulse with a red/orange colour.

Name: Lentil, hulled, dry
Description: Small, lens-shaped, edible pulse with a red/orange, dusty green/brown or black/grey colour.

Name: Lentil, dried, boiled, drained
Description: Small, lens-shaped, edible pulse with a red/orange, dusty green/brown or black/grey colour, cooked by boiling in unsalted water then draining.

Name: Lupin, dehulled, splits, uncooked
Description: Small oval shaped, creamy yellow or white coloured raw beans with or without brown mottling, from the pod of lupin plant species. Includes Australian sweet lupin (Lupinus angustifolius) species. Lupin splits are inner kernels which have been halved and separated from the coat/hull.

Name: Lupin, dehulled, flakes, uncooked
Description: Small oval shaped, creamy yellow or white coloured raw beans with or without brown mottling, from the pod of lupin plant species. Includes Australian sweet lupin (Lupinus angustifolius) species. Lupin flakes are formed by heating and rolling the dehulled lupin split.

Name: Lupin, whole, uncooked
Description: Small oval shaped, creamy yellow or white coloured raw beans with or without brown mottling, from the pod of lupin plant species. Includes Australian sweet lupin (Lupinus angustifolius) species. Whole lupin grain includes the thick seed coat/hull and inner kernel.

Name: Pea, split, dried
Description: Yellow or green field pea with husks removed. Dry and uncooked.

Name: Pea, split, dried, boiled, drained
Description: Yellow or green field pea with husks removed that have been dried, then soaked in water before boiling in unsalted water and draining.

Name: Pea, green, whole, dried
Description: A small round green seed which has been dehydrated after harvest. Uncooked.

Name: Pea, yellow, whole, dried
Description: A small round yellow seed. Uncooked.

Name: Beef, all cuts, separable fat, raw
Description: Raw internal and external separable fat from 13 different cuts of beef from various regions of the carcase.

Name: Beef, all cuts, separable fat, cooked, no added fat
Description: Cooked internal and external separable fat from 13 different cuts of beef from various regions of the carcase. Oven roasted or grilled as purchased, still attached to the lean muscle meat, with no added fat to an internal temperature of 70 degrees celsius or until 'medium', then dissected.

Name: Beef, casserole meat, boneless or bone-in, shin, lean, raw
Description: Boneless raw beef from the shin (or leg) of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only. All possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Beef, casserole meat, boneless or bone-in, shin, lean, casseroled, no added fat
Description: Boneless cooked beef from the shin (or leg) of the carcase. Lean muscle meat only. All possible internal and external separable fat removed after cooking.

Name: Beef, casserole meat, boneless or bone-in, shin, semi-trimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the shin (or leg) of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed.

Name: Beef, casserole meat, boneless or bone-in, shin, semi-trimmed, casseroled, no added fat
Description: Cooked beef from the shin (or leg) of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat. Majority of external fat removed after cooking.

Name: Beef, casserole meat, boneless or bone-in, shin, untrimmed, casseroled, no added fat
Description: Cooked beef from the shin (or leg) of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal fat and external fat attached.

Name: Beef, casserole meat, boneless or bone-in, shin, untrimmed, raw
Description: Raw beef from the shin (or leg) of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with internal and external fat attached.

Name: Beef, boneless dice or strips, lean, raw
Description: Raw beef, purchased diced and likely to be from various regions of the carcase. Lean muscle meat with some inseparable internal fat. All possible internal and external separable fat removed.

Name: Beef, boneless dice or strips, lean, stir-fried, no added fat
